TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hartman, Richard C.
T1  - The Term Structure of Interest Rates and the Demand for Investment*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884586
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 94
IS  - 3
SP  - 591
EP  - 607
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines the question of whether long-term or short-term interest rates should appear in investment demand functions. Three basic models are examined. The first involves a distribution of time lags required to complete investment projects; the second is based on a simple adjustment-costs model; and the third incorporates uncertainty and risk aversion. The major conclusion is that, except for some special cases which are probably quite unrealistic, both long-term and short-term interest rates affect investment demand.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884586
ER  - 



